cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with shape composition using neural networks, which involves computer graphics and computer vision techniques. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel neural network architecture for shape composition, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for generating coherent and plausible 3D shapes, which falls under the category of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category.
